    <body>
      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="J01154H1">
          <head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-J01154H1-headnote-1">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-J01154H1-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-J01154H1-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">I'll tell you a copy of verses. When Mr. <hi rend="italics">St. John</hi> was turned out from being secretary at war, three years ago, he retired to the country: there he was talking of something he would have written over his <hi rend="italics">summer-house</hi>, and a gentleman gave him these verses;</l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-J01154H1-headnote-2">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-J01154H1-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-J01154H1-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1">He swore to me he could hardly bear the jest; for he pretended to retire like a philosopher, though he was but twenty-eight years old: and I believe the thing was true; for he had been a thorough rake. I think the three grave lines do introduce the last well enough. Od so, but I'll go sleep; I sleep early now.</l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-J01154H1-headnote-3">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-J01154H1-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-J01154H1-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-J01154H1-line-1" n="1">From business and the noisy world reti'd,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-J01154H1-line-2" n="2">Nor vex'd by love, nor by ambition fir'd;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-J01154H1-line-3" n="3">Gently I wait the call of <hi rend="italics">Charon</hi>'s boat,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-J01154H1-line-4" n="4">Still drinking like a fish, and ──── like a stoat.</l>
          </lg>
        </div>
      </div>
